results.name: Exponential transform of C(n,5) = A000389.
comment: a(n) is the number of ways of placing n labeled balls into indistinguishable boxes, where in each filled box 5 balls are seen at the top.
a(n) is also the number of forests of labeled rooted trees of height at most 1, with n labels, where each root contains 5 labels.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..500
Index entries for sequences related to rooted trees
mathematica: With[{nmax = 50}, CoefficientList[Series[Exp[Exp[x]*x^5/5!], {x, 0, nmax}], x]] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Nov 21 2017 *)
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Oct 10 2008
